    <learningContentbody>
        <lcObjectives>
            <lcObjectivesGroup id="lcObjectivesGroup_obp_5py_dw">
                <lcObjective>Create and use a conkeyref.</lcObjective>
                <lcObjective>Reference a range of elements with conrefend.</lcObjective>
                <lcObjective>Add an element to a topic with conref push (conaction).</lcObjective>
            </lcObjectivesGroup>
        </lcObjectives>
        <lcDuration>
            <lcTime value="45"/>
        </lcDuration>
        <lcIntro>Content references allow you to reuse a single element (and its content) in other
            topics. This lesson introduces three additional ways you can use content references:<ul
                id="ul_ogy_wdv_qx">
                <li>Conkeyrefs, in which the file path portion of a conref uses a key </li>
                <li>Content reference ranges, which allow content references to pull in multiple
                    elements (and their content)</li>
                <li>Content reference push, which allows maps to insert elements into topics in
                    arbitrary locations</li>
            </ul></lcIntro>
    </learningContentbody>
